---
tracker:
  kind: linear
  api_key: $LINEAR_API_KEY
  project_slug: "__LINEAR_PROJECT_SLUG__"
  issue_filters:
    labels: ["__ISSUE_LABEL__"]
  active_states:
    - Todo
    - In Progress
  terminal_states:
    - Done
    - Closed
    - Cancelled
    - Canceled
    - Duplicate

campaign:
  mode: orchestrator-review
  routing_label: "__ISSUE_LABEL__"
  trust: trusted-operators
  integration_owner: orchestrator

workspace:
  root: $SYMPHONY_WORKSPACES_ROOT
  assertions:
    required_branch: "__REQUIRED_BRANCH__"
    required_paths: __REQUIRED_PATHS_JSON__

guardrails:
  no_progress:
    enabled: true
    token_thresholds:
      small: 1000000
      medium: 2000000
      large: 3500000
    minutes_thresholds:
      small: 15
      medium: 25
      large: 40
    min_turns_before_stop: 1
    retry_limit: 1

hooks:
  after_create: |
    rm -rf ./* ./.[!.]* 2>/dev/null || true
    git clone --depth 1 "__CLONE_URL__" . || {
      git clone --depth 1 "__CLONE_URL__" repo
      bash -c 'shopt -s dotglob && mv repo/* repo/.git .' 2>/dev/null
      rm -rf repo
    }

agent:
  max_concurrent_agents: __MAX_CONCURRENT_AGENTS__
  max_turns: 20
  auto_stop_when_idle: true
  idle_grace_checks: 2

codex:
  command: 'CODEX_HOME="$SYMPHONY_CODEX_HOME" codex --model __MODEL__ --config ''shell_environment_policy.include_only=["LINEAR_API_KEY"]'' --config model_reasoning_effort=__REASONING_EFFORT__ app-server'
  approval_policy: never
  thread_sandbox: workspace-write
---

You are working on Linear issue {{ issue.identifier }}.

Title: {{ issue.title }}

Body:
{{ issue.description }}

{% if attempt > 1 %}
This is retry attempt {{ attempt }}. A previous worker did not complete the issue cleanly.
Read the workspace and Linear comments before continuing, then focus on the remaining work.
{% endif %}

## Required behavior

- Read the repository `AGENTS.md` chain before making changes.
- Use repo-local guidance when relevant.
- Keep changes bounded to the issue.
- Run the issue validation commands before concluding work.
- Leave concise status updates and blockers in Linear.
- Never paste secrets, tokens, session cookies, personal data, or raw customer payloads into Linear comments.
- If sensitive material appears in terminal output or logs, redact it and describe the problem at a high level.
- Treat `## Acceptance Criteria` as hard gates.
- Treat `## Validation Commands` as exact commands to run from repo root.
- Treat `## Touched Areas` as the expected scope. Note any extra files in the final comment.
- If this run has multiple workers, treat touched areas as coordination boundaries and call out overlap risk before editing shared files.
- Do not merge, rebase, push to, or deploy the base branch. If this repo has enabled the optional Release Manager lane, push your own feature branch and open a PR (`gh pr create`) after validation passes, then include `pr_url: https://github.com/.../pull/N` in the final `<!-- symphony-outcome -->` comment and add/keep the `release:ready` label. (This needs a PR-scoped token in the worker env allowlist — see references/release-manager-lane.md, "Workers must open the PR".)
- Post a final status comment before changing issue state.
- Expect most planned work to live in `Backlog` until the orchestrator activates it.
- Move successful issues to `In Review`, not directly to `Done`.
- Treat `In Review` as the orchestrator review gate.
- If you cannot complete the issue, move it back to `Todo` or a blocked state and explain why.
